cs.CG, cs.DS, cs.DM, cs.GT, cs.NA

Reasoning: 
- cs.CG (Computational Geometry) is the most likely category as the paper deals with geometric optimization problems.
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is also likely as the paper presents exact and approximation algorithms for solving the optimization problems.
- cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) is relevant as the problem involves finding rectangles in a discrete setting (a polygon with vertices).
- cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory) may be relevant as the problem involves maximizing area and perimeter, which can be seen as a game-theoretic objective.
- cs.NA (Numerical Analysis) may be relevant as the paper presents algorithms that involve numerical computations.
